			)
			(justify left top)
		)
		(uuid "10dc809b-c166-4dab-b09a-699ce9b6da8d")
	)
	(text_box "VBUS Sensing (not totally necessar since we can assume it's constant, but it's nice to have)\n\nUse a voltage divider to scale the voltage down to an ADC-able range:\nVBUS = Vadc * (R1 + R2) / R2\n\n\nDO IN CONTROL STAGE"
		(exclude_from_sim no)
		(at 128.905 142.875 0)
		(size 58.42 28.575)
		(margins 0.9525 0.9525 0.9525 0.9525)
		(stroke
			(width 0)
			(type solid)
		)
		(fill
			(type none)
		)
		(effects
			(font
				(size 1.27 1.27)
			)
			(justify left top)
		)
		(uuid "2401c15f-675f-4fa4-9d03-7f28f111796b")
	)
	(text_box "Motor Phase Current -> Shunt Resistor -> Current Amplifier -> ADC -> FW, with\nIphase = Vadc / (Gain × Rshunt), where V_shunt = Vadc / Gain\n-> Note that Vadc comes from the op amp AFTER it amplifies the signal\n\nThe result from an OPAMP will be fed into an ADC, then current is calculated. \nADC must be timer triggered, so sampling happens when the mosfet is conducting\n\nFor each phase, need:\n- 1 shunt resistor\n- 2 traces for current sense (OPAMP+ and OPAMP-) [also called Kelvin sense connections]"
		(exclude_from_sim no)
		(at 50.165 139.065 0)
		(size 69.215 39.37)
		(margins 0.9525 0.9525 0.9525 0.9525)
		(stroke
			(width 0)
			(type solid)
		)
		(fill
			(type none)
		)
		(effects
			(font
				(size 1.27 1.27)
			)
			(justify left top)
		)
		(uuid "2d42525d-9d03-4a4c-b3ae-7fb964c30a34")
	)
	(text_box "Gate Resistors (low val) on GHSx and LHSx"
